2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the network is trained end-to-end and validated on publicly available datasets, indicating the use of machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a novel approach to iris verification using a deep learning model. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as iris images are a type of multimedia data. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but still possible as iris verification is often used in security applications.
